---
Umbral archivists in the Gloamvault maintain the most complete external documentation of the Black Ledger period available outside Kowloon's sealed archive.
Documentation accumulated through the Gloamvault's practice of recording what passes through underground spaces — condemned-subject transfer routes passed through Gloamvault-adjacent passages during the Ash-and-Iron years.
Umbral notation is precise: absence is documented. Records show which passages were used, how many people passed through, and when passages were sealed.
The subsequent sealing of transfer routes is documented in neutral terms — confirming transfers occurred and routes were then hidden.
Umbral archivists declined to share documentation, citing a reciprocal disclosure condition: they will share when a city deposits an equivalent volume of institutional testimony.
The condition has not been met. The Gloamvault record is the most comprehensive unsuppressed account of the Black Ledger period, held outside any city's jurisdiction.
